   <conbody>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <note platform="SDC" class="- topic/note ">This option is only possible in redundant
systems with individual batteries.</note>
         <p otherprops="typeR" class="- topic/p ">A redundant
system has two <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">output isolation switches</ph>
            <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">rectifier output switches</ph>. This makes it
possible for one unit to supply the full load or to isolate one unit.
With an optional couple switch between it is possible to separate
the units to function as single systems and supply individual loads.<note class="- topic/note ">The system output is not redundant if one or more of the switches
(couple or output isolation) are open.</note>
         </p>
         <p otherprops="typeD" class="- topic/p ">In a dual system each unit has an output breaker. With an optional
couple switch between the output breakers it is possible switch over
both loads to a single unit.<note class="- topic/note ">In a dual system the units can work
in parallel, but the redundancy of the load is not ensured.</note>
         </p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">For operation instructions see chapter <xref href="How_to_Operate_the_Couple_Switch_in_a_Redundant_or_Dual_System_CPT_0000361406.dita"
                  scope="local"
                  type="concept"
                  class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
